JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways is still operating at a loss.The airline is projecting losses in excess of R800-million for the 2017-2018 financial year.READ: SAA will get cash injection this year, says Treasury DGThe embattled airline's admitted it s failed to meet its budgeted revenue for the past three years. SAA's ongoing losses means it's still heavily reliant on borrowing to fund operational costs.Other factors such as rising oil and fuel prices and intense competition from non-African airlines and low-cost carriers have contributed to the parastatal's woes.eNCA